1
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:45,922
Shit.

2
00:03:41,587 --> 00:03:42,952
[car approaching]

3
00:04:26,131 --> 00:04:27,860
You pair of deuces lookin' for work...

4
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:31,300
l suggest you get your scrawny asses in here pronto.

5
00:04:44,182 --> 00:04:45,911
(Aguirre) Up on Brokeback...

6
00:04:45,984 --> 00:04:48,748
the Forest Service has got designated campsites...

7
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:50,481
on the allotments.

8
00:04:50,555 --> 00:04:54,548
Them camps can be 3, 4 miles from where we pasture the woollies.

9
00:04:54,626 --> 00:04:58,084
Bad predator loss if there's nobody lookin' after 'em at night.

10
00:04:58,163 --> 00:05:01,860
Now, what l want is a camp tender...

11
00:05:02,934 --> 00:05:06,233
to stay in the main camp, where the Forest Service says.

12
00:05:06,305 --> 00:05:07,932
But the herder...

13
00:05:08,073 --> 00:05:11,042
he's gonna pitch a pup tent on the QT with the sheep...

14
00:05:11,109 --> 00:05:13,168
and he's gonna sleep there.

15
00:05:13,245 --> 00:05:16,009
You eat your supper and breakfast in camp...

16
00:05:16,081 --> 00:05:19,107
but you sleep with the sheep 100%.

17
00:05:19,785 --> 00:05:22,276
No fire, don't leave no sign.

18
00:05:23,021 --> 00:05:24,511
You roll up that tent every mornin'...

19
00:05:24,589 --> 00:05:26,022
in case Forest Service snoops around.

20
00:05:26,091 --> 00:05:27,388
[phone ringing]

21
00:05:28,193 --> 00:05:29,285
Yeah?

22
00:05:31,163 --> 00:05:32,187
No.

23
00:05:33,398 --> 00:05:34,490
{man chattering on phone]

24
00:05:34,566 --> 00:05:35,555
No!

25
00:05:38,136 --> 00:05:40,127
Not on your fuckin' life.

26
00:05:43,141 --> 00:05:46,941
You got your dogs, your .30-30, you sleep there.

27
00:05:47,546 --> 00:05:51,607
Last summer l had goddamn near 25% loss. l don't want that again.

28
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:53,208
You.

29
00:05:54,753 --> 00:05:57,483
Fridays at noon, be down at the bridge...

30
00:05:57,889 --> 00:06:00,289
with your grocery list and mules...

31
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:04,056
and somebody with supplies will be there at the pick-up.

32
00:06:06,698 --> 00:06:09,997
Tomorrow mornin' we'll truck you up to the jump-off.

33
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,024
Jack Twist. Ennis.

34
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:45,732
Your folks just stop at Ennis? Del Mar.

35
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:49,670
Well, nice to know you, Ennis Del Mar.

36
00:06:52,811 --> 00:06:54,369
[dog barking]

37
00:07:03,722 --> 00:07:05,622
{man chattering on TV]

38
00:07:08,093 --> 00:07:09,993
My second year up here.

39
00:07:11,229 --> 00:07:14,528
Last year, one storm, the lightnin' killed 42 sheep.

40
00:07:15,734 --> 00:07:18,328
Thought l'd asphyxiate from the smell.

41
00:07:18,737 --> 00:07:23,140
Aguirre got all over my ass, like l was supposed to control the weather.

42
00:07:23,308 --> 00:07:27,438
But beats workin' for my old man. Can't please my old man, no way.

43
00:07:29,147 --> 00:07:32,810
That's why l took to rodeoin'. You ever rodeo?

44
00:07:34,352 --> 00:07:37,253
You know, l mean, once in a while.

45
00:07:37,989 --> 00:07:40,514
When l got the entry fee in my pocket.

46
00:07:40,592 --> 00:07:41,684
Yeah.

47
00:07:43,094 --> 00:07:45,119
Are you from ranch people?

48
00:07:45,263 --> 00:07:46,662
Yeah, l was.

49
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,300
Your folks run you off?

50
00:07:51,470 --> 00:07:54,268
No, they run themselves off. There was...

51
00:07:55,674 --> 00:07:59,007
one curve in the road in 43 miles, and they miss it.

52
00:08:00,679 --> 00:08:03,477
So the bank took the ranch...

53
00:08:03,548 --> 00:08:06,642
and my brother and sister, they raised me, mostly.

54
00:08:09,454 --> 00:08:11,649
[lighter clicking] Shit, that's hard.

55
00:08:16,862 --> 00:08:19,160
Can l? Thank you.

56
00:08:19,231 --> 00:08:20,528
[clears throat]

57
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:24,331
[sheep bleating]

58
00:08:29,107 --> 00:08:31,234
[men chattering]

59
00:08:39,417 --> 00:08:40,645
(Basque) Don't let them stray.

60
00:08:40,719 --> 00:08:42,653
Joe will have your ass if you do.

61
00:08:42,721 --> 00:08:45,349
Only thing, don't never order soup.

62
00:08:45,857 --> 00:08:48,257
Them soup boxes are hard to pack.

63
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,660
Well, l don't eat soup.

64
00:08:50,729 --> 00:08:52,094
[horse neighing]

65
00:08:52,898 --> 00:08:54,695
[dogs barking]

66
00:08:55,934 --> 00:08:59,631
You wanna watch it there. That horse has a low startle point.

67
00:09:00,171 --> 00:09:02,867
Doubt there's a filly that could throw me.

68
00:09:03,508 --> 00:09:07,205
Let's git, unless you wanna sit around tyin' knots all day.

69
00:09:15,787 --> 00:09:17,584
@@[Ennis whistling]

70
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,096
[Jack chattering]

71
00:09:36,107 --> 00:09:37,699
[dog barking]

72
00:10:00,565 --> 00:10:02,863
[sheep bleating]

73
00:10:40,271 --> 00:10:41,829
[Ennis sawing]

74
00:10:47,379 --> 00:10:48,937
[water rushing]

75
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:51,467
Oh, shit.

76
00:11:51,810 --> 00:11:53,539
Can't wait till l get my own spread...

77
00:11:53,611 --> 00:11:56,876
and l won't have to put up with Joe Aguirre's crap no more.

78
00:11:57,449 --> 00:11:59,679
l'm savin' for a place myself.

79
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:06,086
Alma and me, we're gonna get married when l come down off this mountain.

80
00:12:06,191 --> 00:12:09,354
Shit, that stay with the sheep, no fire bullshit.

81
00:12:10,829 --> 00:12:14,663
Aguirre got no right makin' us do somethin' against the rules.

82
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:27,075
[horse snuffling]

83
00:12:35,487 --> 00:12:36,954
[egging]

84
00:12:47,866 --> 00:12:50,198
[thunder rumbling]

85
00:13:04,015 --> 00:13:05,505
No more beans.

86
00:13:39,584 --> 00:13:41,779
Damn. Shit!

87
00:13:45,657 --> 00:13:47,784
l don't know. Something wrong?

88
00:13:49,093 --> 00:13:50,287
Yeah, so what....

89
00:13:50,361 --> 00:13:52,989
Why didn't we get the powdered milk and the spuds?

90
00:13:53,064 --> 00:13:54,554
That's all we got.

91
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:56,394
Well....

92
00:13:57,235 --> 00:13:58,930
Here's next week's.

93
00:14:01,439 --> 00:14:04,897
Thought you didn't eat soup. Yeah, well, l'm sick of beans.

94
00:14:04,976 --> 00:14:07,877
Too early in the summer to be sick of beans.

95
00:14:10,648 --> 00:14:11,876
Come on.

96
00:14:24,562 --> 00:14:26,086
@@[humming]

97
00:14:34,772 --> 00:14:36,330
Come on. Come on.

98
00:14:38,276 --> 00:14:39,368
[growling]

99
00:14:39,477 --> 00:14:41,138
[horse neighing]

100
00:14:42,046 --> 00:14:43,980
[bear roaring]

101
00:14:47,719 --> 00:14:49,346
Hold on. Whoa, whoa!

102
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,978
[mules braying]

103
00:14:52,991 --> 00:14:53,980
Shit.

104
00:14:55,093 --> 00:14:57,084
Whoa. Come back here!

105
00:14:58,096 --> 00:14:59,461
[horse snuffling]

106
00:15:35,566 --> 00:15:37,090
Whoa there, whoa.

107
00:15:37,235 --> 00:15:38,998
All right. Fuck it.

108
00:15:40,471 --> 00:15:42,371
(Ennis) Okay, you bastard.

109
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:47,143
Where the hell you been?

110
00:15:47,211 --> 00:15:49,702
Been up with the sheep all day, l get down here hungry as hell...

111
00:15:49,781 --> 00:15:51,715
and all l find is beans.

112
00:15:51,816 --> 00:15:53,181
[muttering]

113
00:15:54,919 --> 00:15:56,045
[pans clattering]

114
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:58,315
What in the hell happened, Ennis?

115
00:15:58,589 --> 00:16:00,989
l come on a bear is what happened.

116
00:16:01,259 --> 00:16:03,523
Goddamn horse spooked and the mules took off...

117
00:16:03,594 --> 00:16:05,528
and scattered food everywhere.

118
00:16:06,097 --> 00:16:09,863
Beans is about all we got left. Got whiskey or somethin'?

119
00:16:15,373 --> 00:16:16,863
Dumb-ass mule.

120
00:16:21,779 --> 00:16:25,010
l can't believe that. God damn.

121
00:16:26,617 --> 00:16:28,209
Let me see.

122
00:16:34,192 --> 00:16:35,284
Shit.

123
00:16:35,827 --> 00:16:39,285
Well, we gotta do somethin' about this food situation.

124
00:16:39,731 --> 00:16:42,165
Maybe l'll shoot one of the sheep.

125
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:44,901
Yeah, what if Aguirre finds out, huh?

126
00:16:44,969 --> 00:16:46,937
We're supposed to guard the sheep, not eat 'em.

127
00:16:47,005 --> 00:16:50,463
What's the matter with you? There are a thousand of 'em.

128
00:16:51,609 --> 00:16:53,474
l'll stick with beans.

129
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:57,270
Well, l won't.

130
00:17:04,689 --> 00:17:05,815
[gun fires]

131
00:17:09,927 --> 00:17:11,087
[whooping]

132
00:17:11,162 --> 00:17:12,186
Yeah!

133
00:17:12,263 --> 00:17:14,891
Gettin' tired of your dumb-ass missin'.

134
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:16,566
[laughing] Let's get a move on.

135
00:17:16,634 --> 00:17:19,603
Don't want the Game and Fish to catch us with no elk.

136
00:17:44,429 --> 00:17:46,590
Come on. Shit.

137
00:17:53,638 --> 00:17:56,163
Yeah, l'm commutin' four hours a day.

138
00:17:57,008 --> 00:18:00,102
l come in for breakfast, l go back to the sheep.

139
00:18:00,478 --> 00:18:02,605
Evenin', get 'em bedded down.

140
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:05,444
Come in for supper, go back to the sheep.

141
00:18:06,484 --> 00:18:09,544
Spend half the night checkin' for damn coyotes.

142
00:18:10,354 --> 00:18:12,982
Aguirre got no right to make me do this.

143
00:18:15,793 --> 00:18:18,091
You wanna switch? l wouldn't mind sleepin' out there.

144
00:18:18,162 --> 00:18:21,996
That ain't the point. The point is, we both ought to be in this camp.

145
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:25,928
Goddamn pup tent smells like cat piss or worse.

146
00:18:26,704 --> 00:18:29,036
l wouldn't mind bein' out there.

147
00:18:32,376 --> 00:18:34,708
Well, l'm happy to switch with you...

148
00:18:34,779 --> 00:18:37,373
but l warn you, l can't cook worth a damn.

149
00:18:37,982 --> 00:18:40,815
l am pretty good with a can opener, though.

150
00:18:41,719 --> 00:18:44,210
You can't be no worse than me, then.

151
00:18:45,089 --> 00:18:46,488
Here you go.

152
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:50,552
[coughs]

153
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:58,933
You won't get much sleep, l'll tell you that.

154
00:18:59,003 --> 00:19:00,732
Yup. Come on.

155
00:19:00,805 --> 00:19:02,102
[clucks tongue]

156
00:19:11,782 --> 00:19:13,340
[bird calling]

157
00:19:14,619 --> 00:19:16,348
[horse snuffling]

158
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:22,426
Shot a coyote up there.

159
00:19:23,361 --> 00:19:27,058
lt's a big son of a bitch. He had balls on him the size of apples.

160
00:19:28,032 --> 00:19:30,899
He looked like he could eat himself a camel.

161
00:19:32,403 --> 00:19:34,701
You want some of this hot water?

162
00:19:36,507 --> 00:19:37,940
[mutters]

163
00:19:38,409 --> 00:19:39,933
lt's all yours.

164
00:20:01,999 --> 00:20:03,830
[urinating]

165
00:20:06,304 --> 00:20:07,396
Mmm.

166
00:20:19,116 --> 00:20:21,107
l don't rodeo much myself.

167
00:20:21,886 --> 00:20:23,046
l mean, what's the point...

168
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,782
of ridin' some piece of stock for eight seconds?

169
00:20:25,856 --> 00:20:28,882
Money's a good point. True enough.

170
00:20:30,361 --> 00:20:33,057
lf you don't get stomped winnin' it, huh?

171
00:20:33,197 --> 00:20:34,289
Yeah.

172
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:39,161
Well, my old man, he was a bull rider.

173
00:20:40,905 --> 00:20:42,236
Thank you.

174
00:20:43,007 --> 00:20:45,202
Pretty well-known in his day.

175
00:20:45,610 --> 00:20:48,204
Though he kept his secrets to himself.

176
00:20:49,614 --> 00:20:53,141
Never taught me a thing, never once come to see me ride.

177
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:01,588
[grunts]

178
00:21:04,695 --> 00:21:07,391
Your brother and sister do right by you?

179
00:21:08,032 --> 00:21:11,468
They did the best they could after my folks was gone.

180
00:21:13,337 --> 00:21:16,170
Considerin' they didn't leave us nothin'...

181
00:21:16,507 --> 00:21:18,600
but $24 in a coffee can.

182
00:21:20,177 --> 00:21:22,543
l got me a year of high school.

183
00:21:23,314 --> 00:21:26,511
That was before the transmission went on the pickup.

184
00:21:29,287 --> 00:21:32,984
And then my sis left. She married a roughneck, moved to Casper.

185
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:35,854
And me and my brother...

186
00:21:35,926 --> 00:21:39,453
we went and got ourselves some work on a ranch up near Worland.

187
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:42,465
Till l was 19. Then he got married.

188
00:21:45,102 --> 00:21:47,036
And no more room for me.

189
00:21:50,441 --> 00:21:54,070
That's how come me end up here.

190
00:22:04,255 --> 00:22:05,347
What?

191
00:22:07,158 --> 00:22:11,060
Man, that's more words than you've spoke in the past two weeks.

192
00:22:11,929 --> 00:22:14,762
Hell, that's the most l've spoke in a year.

193
00:22:20,738 --> 00:22:23,070
But my dad, he was a fine roper.

194
00:22:24,175 --> 00:22:25,472
Didn't rodeo much, though.

195
00:22:25,543 --> 00:22:28,137
He thought rodeo cowboys was all fuck-ups.

196
00:22:31,048 --> 00:22:32,709
The hell they are.

197
00:22:34,385 --> 00:22:35,613
Well....

198
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:40,817
[exclaims]

199
00:22:41,525 --> 00:22:42,753
[whooping] There you go.

200
00:22:42,827 --> 00:22:44,488
[exclaiming]

201
00:22:44,562 --> 00:22:48,328
l'm spurrin' his guts out! Wavin' to the girls in the stands!

202
00:22:48,399 --> 00:22:51,960
He's kickin' me to high heaven, but he don't jackboard me! No!

203
00:22:52,036 --> 00:22:53,367
[clattering]

204
00:22:54,372 --> 00:22:55,566
[laughing]

205
00:22:56,173 --> 00:22:58,164
l think my dad was right.

206
00:23:02,646 --> 00:23:04,409
[bleating]

207
00:23:13,224 --> 00:23:14,691
[bird calls]

208
00:23:37,748 --> 00:23:39,545
@@[harmonica playing]

209
00:23:43,387 --> 00:23:45,252
Tent don't look right.

210
00:23:45,956 --> 00:23:48,789
Well, it ain't goin' nowhere. Let it be.

211
00:23:50,728 --> 00:23:53,196
That harmonica don't sound quite right either.

212
00:23:53,264 --> 00:23:56,700
That's 'cause it got kind of flattened when that mare threw me.

213
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:58,359
Oh, yeah? Yeah.

214
00:23:58,969 --> 00:24:01,870
l thought you said that mare couldn't throw you.

215
00:24:01,939 --> 00:24:03,429
She got lucky.

216
00:24:04,875 --> 00:24:08,402
Yeah, well, if l got lucky, that harmonica would've broke in two.

217
00:24:08,579 --> 00:24:09,739
[grunts]

218
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,342
[chuckling]

219
00:24:11,882 --> 00:24:16,114
(Jack) @ l know l shall meet you on that final day @

220
00:24:16,687 --> 00:24:21,681
@ Water-walking Jesus, take me away! @@

221
00:24:21,759 --> 00:24:22,919
[drumming]

222
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,988
Very good. Oh, yeah.

223
00:24:26,197 --> 00:24:29,291
My mama, she believes in the Pentecost.

224
00:24:29,366 --> 00:24:30,628
Oh, yeah?

225
00:24:32,803 --> 00:24:34,771
What exactly is the Pentecost?

226
00:24:34,839 --> 00:24:37,603
l mean, my folks, they was Methodist.

227
00:24:39,043 --> 00:24:40,533
The Pentecost.

228
00:24:40,845 --> 00:24:43,336
l don't know, l don't know what the Pentecost is.

229
00:24:43,414 --> 00:24:47,874
Mom never explained it to me. l guess it's when the world ends...

230
00:24:48,052 --> 00:24:51,112
and fellas like you and me, we march off to hell.

231
00:24:52,289 --> 00:24:53,881
Speak for yourself.

232
00:24:53,958 --> 00:24:57,485
You may be a sinner, but l ain't yet had the opportunity.

233
00:25:00,097 --> 00:25:01,428
Thank you.

234
00:25:04,301 --> 00:25:06,201
[bottle clinking] (Ennis) Shit!

235
00:25:08,138 --> 00:25:10,038
l'm gonna go up to the sheep now.

236
00:25:10,107 --> 00:25:11,597
(Jack) Give 'em hell.

237
00:25:16,013 --> 00:25:17,640
[horse snuffling]

238
00:25:17,715 --> 00:25:19,239
[slurring] No, l'm....

239
00:25:21,385 --> 00:25:24,912
You can hardly stand. lt's too late to go to them sheep.

240
00:25:28,692 --> 00:25:30,683
Well, you got an extra blanket?

241
00:25:30,828 --> 00:25:34,662
l'll just roll up out here, grab 40 winks...

242
00:25:35,065 --> 00:25:37,465
and l'll ride out at first light.

243
00:25:41,505 --> 00:25:44,201
You'll freeze your ass off when that fire dies down.

244
00:25:44,275 --> 00:25:45,572
Oh, that's good.

245
00:25:45,643 --> 00:25:47,611
You're better off sleepin' in the tent.

246
00:25:47,678 --> 00:25:48,770
Yeah.

247
00:25:50,447 --> 00:25:51,778
All right.

248
00:26:04,762 --> 00:26:06,127
[shivering]

249
00:26:13,203 --> 00:26:14,693
[Jack sighing]

250
00:26:28,185 --> 00:26:30,517
Ennis! What?

251
00:26:31,155 --> 00:26:33,885
Just quit your yammerin' and get in here!

252
00:26:41,699 --> 00:26:43,166
[pans clattering]

253
00:27:31,915 --> 00:27:34,145
[blankets rustling]

254
00:27:35,219 --> 00:27:37,346
[Jack whispering] Come on, come on.

255
00:27:46,597 --> 00:27:48,326
(Ennis) What are you doin'?

256
00:27:57,474 --> 00:27:59,533
[both breathing heavily]

257
00:28:05,282 --> 00:28:06,806
[belt clinking]

258
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:19,690
[both moaning]

259
00:28:20,597 --> 00:28:23,327
[gasping]

260
00:28:38,515 --> 00:28:39,880
[Ennis grunting]

261
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:54,561
[birds chirping]

262
00:29:55,325 --> 00:29:57,054
See you for supper.

263
00:29:58,462 --> 00:29:59,952
Yeah. Come on.

264
00:30:15,712 --> 00:30:17,942
[wind whistling]

