01:35:39,094 --> 01:35:40,652
to fix that pickup.

1031
01:35:40,729 --> 01:35:42,856
Well, he's never been very mechanical, though.

1032
01:35:43,298 --> 01:35:45,061
[crickets chirping]

1033
01:35:45,734 --> 01:35:47,599
Come over here and ask....

1034
01:35:47,770 --> 01:35:49,567
[people chattering]

1035
01:35:54,376 --> 01:35:56,503
You ever notice how a woman will powder her nose...

1036
01:35:56,578 --> 01:35:58,512
before she goes to a party?

1037
01:35:58,580 --> 01:36:02,016
And then she'll powder it again once the party's over.

1038
01:36:02,317 --> 01:36:05,809
l mean, why powder your nose just to go home and go to bed?

1039
01:36:05,888 --> 01:36:07,219
Don't know.

1040
01:36:08,057 --> 01:36:09,422
Even if l wanted to know...

1041
01:36:09,491 --> 01:36:12,756
l couldn't get a word in with Lashawn long enough to ask.

1042
01:36:12,828 --> 01:36:16,161
Woman talks a blue streak. Lively little gal.

1043
01:36:18,967 --> 01:36:20,332
[clearing throat]

1044
01:36:24,106 --> 01:36:26,199
You'll like working for Roy Taylor.

1045
01:36:26,275 --> 01:36:29,472
He's solid, Roy. Yeah, Roy. He's a good old boy.

1046
01:36:34,883 --> 01:36:37,716
He's got a little cabin down on Lake Kemp.

1047
01:36:39,054 --> 01:36:41,454
Got a crappie house, little boat.

1048
01:36:41,990 --> 01:36:44,515
Said l could use it whenever l want.

1049
01:36:48,263 --> 01:36:50,891
We ought to go down there some weekend.

1050
01:36:51,734 --> 01:36:54,168
Drink a little whiskey, fish some.

1051
01:36:55,571 --> 01:36:57,835
Get away, you know?

1052
01:37:01,043 --> 01:37:02,533
(LaShawn) That was right out of SMU.

1053
01:37:02,611 --> 01:37:05,079
l could've had my pick of pretty much any job in North Dallas.

1054
01:37:05,147 --> 01:37:07,513
So my pick was Neiman Marcus, which was a disaster...

1055
01:37:07,583 --> 01:37:10,677
because, honey, where clothes is concerned, l got no resistance.

1056
01:37:10,753 --> 01:37:14,018
l was spending more than l made. More than Randall ever will make.

1057
01:37:14,089 --> 01:37:15,078
We come out here...

1058
01:37:15,157 --> 01:37:17,250
thinkin' that ranchin' was still big hats and Marlboros.

1059
01:37:17,326 --> 01:37:19,260
Boy, were we behind the times.

1060
01:37:35,878 --> 01:37:38,073
(Ennis) Hey there, Junior. You ready?

1061
01:37:38,647 --> 01:37:39,636
[truck door closing]

1062
01:37:39,715 --> 01:37:42,183
@@{country music pIaying]

1063
01:37:53,328 --> 01:37:55,057
(Cassie) What do you think?

1064
01:37:55,898 --> 01:37:59,197
Your daddy ever gonna see fit to settle down again?

1065
01:38:00,536 --> 01:38:03,903
Don't know. Maybe he's not the marrying kind.

1066
01:38:06,875 --> 01:38:08,604
You don't think so?

1067
01:38:09,278 --> 01:38:11,906
Or you don't think l'm the one for him?

1068
01:38:12,014 --> 01:38:13,845
[people chattering]

1069
01:38:14,683 --> 01:38:16,412
You're good enough.

1070
01:38:16,485 --> 01:38:19,318
@@{MeIissa by The Allman Brothers playing]

1071
01:38:21,490 --> 01:38:24,687
You don't say much, but you get your point across.

1072
01:38:26,862 --> 01:38:29,194
Sorry. l didn't mean to be rude.

1073
01:38:30,098 --> 01:38:31,725
[Ennis clearing throat]

1074
01:38:32,100 --> 01:38:33,192
All right.

1075
01:38:34,036 --> 01:38:36,561
You're stayin' on your feet, cowboy.

1076
01:38:37,673 --> 01:38:39,163
Excuse me, darling.

1077
01:39:02,064 --> 01:39:05,727
So l'll pick you and Jenny up next weekend, after church.

1078
01:39:07,202 --> 01:39:08,294
Fine.

1079
01:39:11,974 --> 01:39:13,464
You all right?

1080
01:39:14,776 --> 01:39:15,834
Yes.

1081
01:39:17,045 --> 01:39:18,512
Are you sure?

1082
01:39:21,783 --> 01:39:24,946
Daddy, l was thinking, what with the new baby and all...

1083
01:39:25,020 --> 01:39:27,420
Ma and Monroe have been awful strict on me.

1084
01:39:27,489 --> 01:39:29,582
More on me than Jenny even.

1085
01:39:30,492 --> 01:39:32,824
l was thinkin', maybe l could....

1086
01:39:34,997 --> 01:39:37,397
Maybe l could come stay with you.

1087
01:39:38,567 --> 01:39:41,400
l'd be an awful good help, l know l would.

1088
01:39:41,837 --> 01:39:44,829
Now, you know l ain't set up for that.

1089
01:39:46,675 --> 01:39:48,802
With the roundup comin'...

1090
01:39:49,478 --> 01:39:51,275
l won't ever be home.

1091
01:39:52,781 --> 01:39:54,646
lt's all right, Daddy.

1092
01:39:54,917 --> 01:39:58,876
l'm not sayin' that l wouldn't-- lt's all right, l understand.

1093
01:40:01,256 --> 01:40:03,486
Well, see you on Sunday, then.

1094
01:40:04,459 --> 01:40:05,517
Bye.

1095
01:40:08,063 --> 01:40:09,655
Bye, sweetheart.

1096
01:40:39,194 --> 01:40:41,492
Going to snow tonight for sure.

1097
01:40:42,731 --> 01:40:43,789
Yup.

1098
01:40:51,440 --> 01:40:54,898
All this time and you ain't found nobody else to marry?

1099
01:40:56,712 --> 01:40:58,111
l been puttin' the blocks...

1100
01:40:58,180 --> 01:41:01,047
to a good-lookin' little gal over in Riverton.

1101
01:41:02,551 --> 01:41:06,453
She's a waitress. Wants to go to nursing school or somethin'.

1102
01:41:09,424 --> 01:41:10,789
l don't know.

1103
01:41:14,296 --> 01:41:16,321
What about you and Lureen?

1104
01:41:18,834 --> 01:41:21,632
Lureen's good at making hard deals in the machinery business...

1105
01:41:21,703 --> 01:41:24,137
but as far as our marriage goes...

1106
01:41:24,673 --> 01:41:26,903
we could do it over the phone.

1107
01:41:36,818 --> 01:41:39,548
l kind of got this thing going with...

1108
01:41:40,455 --> 01:41:43,117
a ranch foreman's wife over in Rutters.

1109
01:41:43,492 --> 01:41:45,153
What? l'm bound to get shot...

1110
01:41:45,227 --> 01:41:48,560
by Lureen or her husband each time l slip off to see her.

1111
01:41:49,731 --> 01:41:51,756
You probably deserve it.

1112
01:41:58,707 --> 01:42:00,265
Tell you what.

1113
01:42:05,313 --> 01:42:06,837
The truth is...

1114
01:42:13,822 --> 01:42:17,121
sometimes l miss you so much, l can hardly stand it.

1115
01:42:33,475 --> 01:42:34,965
[truck door closing]

1116
01:42:59,401 --> 01:43:02,131
l guess l'll head up on to Lightning Flat.

1117
01:43:03,505 --> 01:43:05,803
See the folks for a day or two.

1118
01:43:11,713 --> 01:43:14,910
There's somethin' l been meanin' to tell you, bud.

1119
01:43:19,020 --> 01:43:22,512
Well, it's likely November before l can come out here again.

1120
01:43:25,927 --> 01:43:30,159
After we ship stock and before winter feedin' starts again.

1121
01:43:34,069 --> 01:43:35,297
November.

1122
01:43:39,374 --> 01:43:42,104
What in the hell ever happened to August?

1123
01:43:43,011 --> 01:43:44,000
Well....

1124
01:43:47,182 --> 01:43:48,672
Christ, Ennis.

1125
01:43:54,656 --> 01:43:58,820
You know, you had a fucking week to say some little word about this.

1126
01:44:01,329 --> 01:44:03,763
Why is it we're always in the friggin' cold?

1127
01:44:03,832 --> 01:44:06,426
We ought to go south where it's warm, you know!

1128
01:44:06,501 --> 01:44:08,492
We ought to go to Mexico.

1129
01:44:09,337 --> 01:44:10,531
Mexico?

1130
01:44:11,873 --> 01:44:14,364
Hell, Jack, you know me. About all the travelin' l ever done...

1131
01:44:14,442 --> 01:44:17,502
is around a coffee pot, looking for the handle.

1132
01:44:19,948 --> 01:44:22,280
(Ennis) Come on, Jack. Lighten up on me.

1133
01:44:24,386 --> 01:44:26,354
We can hunt in November.

1134
01:44:27,189 --> 01:44:28,918
Kill us a nice elk.

1135
01:44:31,459 --> 01:44:33,324
l'll try if l can get Don Wroe's cabin again.

1136
01:44:33,395 --> 01:44:36,091
We had a good time that year, didn't we?

1137
01:44:38,733 --> 01:44:41,429
There's never enough time, never enough.

1138
01:44:45,907 --> 01:44:47,636
You know, friend...

1139
01:44:48,743 --> 01:44:52,201
this is a goddamn bitch of an unsatisfactory situation.

1140
01:44:53,281 --> 01:44:56,910
You used to come away easy. Now it's like seein' the Pope.

1141
01:44:59,888 --> 01:45:01,651
Jack, l got to work.

1142
01:45:04,759 --> 01:45:07,660
ln them earlier days, l'd just quit the job.

1143
01:45:10,398 --> 01:45:11,729
You....

1144
01:45:12,400 --> 01:45:15,665
You forget what it's like bein' broke all the time.

1145
01:45:19,274 --> 01:45:21,572
You ever hear of child support?

1146
01:45:25,447 --> 01:45:27,779
l'll tell you this, l can't quit this one...

1147
01:45:27,849 --> 01:45:29,840
and l can't get the time off.

1148
01:45:33,788 --> 01:45:35,779
lt was hard enough gettin' this time.

1149
01:45:35,857 --> 01:45:37,586
The trade-off was August.

1150
01:45:41,730 --> 01:45:43,595
Well, you got a better idea?

1151
01:45:46,401 --> 01:45:47,800
l did, once.

1152
01:45:50,005 --> 01:45:51,495
(Ennis) You did, once.

1153
01:45:56,344 --> 01:45:58,869
Well, have you been to Mexico, Jack Twist?

1154
01:46:01,549 --> 01:46:05,076
'Cause l hear what they got in Mexico for boys like you.

1155
01:46:06,821 --> 01:46:10,382
Hell, yes, l've been to Mexico. ls that a fucking problem?

1156
01:46:18,466 --> 01:46:21,867
l'm going to tell you this one time, Jack fucking Twist.

1157
01:46:21,936 --> 01:46:23,699
And l ain't foolin'.

1158
01:46:25,040 --> 01:46:28,703
What l don't know, all them things that l don't know...

1159
01:46:29,110 --> 01:46:32,011
could get you killed if l come to know them.

1160
01:46:36,184 --> 01:46:37,708
l ain't jokin'.

1161
01:46:42,524 --> 01:46:45,186
Yeah, well try this one, and l'll say it just once.

1162
01:46:45,260 --> 01:46:47,956
Go ahead! l'll tell you what.

1163
01:46:48,029 --> 01:46:49,496
We could have had a good life together.

1164
01:46:49,564 --> 01:46:52,761
Fucking real good life. Had us a place of our own!

1165
01:46:53,802 --> 01:46:55,861
But you didn't want it, Ennis.

1166
01:46:55,937 --> 01:46:58,735
So what we got now is Brokeback Mountain!

1167
01:47:00,975 --> 01:47:04,274
Everything's built on that! That's all we got, boy. Fucking all.

1168
01:47:04,346 --> 01:47:06,974
So l hope you know that, if you don't never know the rest!

1169
01:47:07,048 --> 01:47:09,312
God damn it. You count the damn few times...

1170
01:47:09,384 --> 01:47:11,181
that we have been together in nearly 20 years...

1171
01:47:11,252 --> 01:47:13,379
and you measure the short fucking leash you keep me on...

1172
01:47:13,455 --> 01:47:16,083
and then you ask me about Mexico and you tell me you'll kill me...

1173
01:47:16,157 --> 01:47:19,217
for needin' somethin' l don't hardly never get!

1174
01:47:21,796 --> 01:47:24,731
You have no idea how bad it gets!

1175
01:47:28,269 --> 01:47:31,204
And l'm not you! l can't make it...

1176
01:47:31,272 --> 01:47:34,799
on a couple of high-altitude fucks once or twice a year!

1177
01:47:37,379 --> 01:47:39,677
You are too much for me, Ennis.

1178
01:47:40,382 --> 01:47:42,509
You son of a whoreson bitch!

1179
01:47:44,686 --> 01:47:46,916
l wish l knew how to quit you!

1180
01:47:49,557 --> 01:47:51,286
Then why don't you?

1181
01:47:54,229 --> 01:47:56,663
Why don't you just let me be, huh?

1182
01:47:58,733 --> 01:48:01,725
lt's because of you, Jack, that l'm like this.

1183
01:48:05,373 --> 01:48:06,772
l'm nothin'.

1184
01:48:07,442 --> 01:48:08,841
l'm nowhere.

1185
01:48:13,515 --> 01:48:16,143
lt's okay. Get the fuck off me!

1186
01:48:16,551 --> 01:48:17,950
[grunting]

1187
01:48:18,486 --> 01:48:19,885
[sobbing]

1188
01:48:23,224 --> 01:48:25,818
lt's all right. lt's all right.

1189
01:48:26,895 --> 01:48:28,487
Damn you, Ennis.

1190
01:48:29,831 --> 01:48:32,425
l just can't stand this anymore, Jack.

1191
01:48:42,944 --> 01:48:46,402
Come on now, you're sleepin' on your feet like a horse.

1192
01:48:48,750 --> 01:48:51,913
My mama used to say that to me when l was little.

1193
01:48:52,954 --> 01:48:54,649
And sing to me.

1194
01:48:55,990 --> 01:48:57,787
@@[humming]

1195
01:49:08,503 --> 01:49:09,902
l got to go.

1196
01:49:12,841 --> 01:49:14,775
See you in the morning.

1197
01:49:55,683 --> 01:49:57,776
@@{country music pIaying]

1198
01:50:04,792 --> 01:50:06,692
[phone ringing]

1199
01:50:09,931 --> 01:50:11,262
Excuse me.

1200
01:50:16,337 --> 01:50:17,395
Hey.

1201
01:50:18,373 --> 01:50:19,863
Ennis Del Mar.

1202
01:50:23,444 --> 01:50:24,968
Where you been?

1203
01:50:26,948 --> 01:50:28,472
Here and there.

1204
01:50:31,152 --> 01:50:34,280
l left word for you with Steve at the ranch.

1205
01:50:35,189 --> 01:50:38,556
And you must've got those notes l left at your place.

1206
01:50:42,363 --> 01:50:45,161
Looks like l got the message, in any case.

1207
01:50:47,402 --> 01:50:48,494
Carl?

1208
01:50:50,338 --> 01:50:52,306
Yeah, Carl's nice.

1209
01:50:53,074 --> 01:50:54,564
He even talks.

1210
01:50:57,779 --> 01:50:59,246
Good for you.

1211
01:51:01,616 --> 01:51:02,708
Yeah.

1212
01:51:05,720 --> 01:51:07,119
Good for me.

1213
01:51:13,561 --> 01:51:15,859
l don't get you, Ennis Del Mar.

1214
01:51:21,202 --> 01:51:22,533
l'm sorry.

1215
01:51:31,012 --> 01:51:33,537
l was probably no fun anyways, was l?

1216
01:51:37,018 --> 01:51:39,953
Ennis, girls don't fall in love with fun.

1217
01:51:44,959 --> 01:51:46,756
[sobbing]

1218
01:51:50,598 --> 01:51:52,031
[door closing]

1219
01:52:16,858 --> 01:52:18,348
[telephone ringing]

1220
01:52:22,697 --> 01:52:26,360
(Lureen) Hello. HeIIo, this is Ennis DeI Mar.

1221
01:52:29,671 --> 01:52:31,298
Who? Who is this?

1222
01:52:32,874 --> 01:52:35,672
Ennis Del Mar. l'm an old buddy of Jack's.

1223
01:52:36,778 --> 01:52:38,871
(Lureen) Jack used to mention you.

1224
01:52:39,247 --> 01:52:42,944
You're the fishing buddy or the hunting buddy, l know that.

1225
01:52:44,018 --> 01:52:45,781
Would have let you know what happened...

1226
01:52:45,853 --> 01:52:48,378
but l wasn't sure about your name or address.

1227
01:52:48,456 --> 01:52:51,391
Jack kept his friends' addresses in his head.

1228
01:52:53,294 --> 01:52:56,229
That's why l'm callin', to see what happened.

1229
01:52:58,232 --> 01:52:59,756
Oh, yeah.

1230
01:53:02,203 --> 01:53:05,138
Jack was pumpin' up a flat on the truck...

1231
01:53:05,239 --> 01:53:07,969
out on a back road, when the tire blew up.

1232
01:53:08,109 --> 01:53:11,010
The rim of the tire slammed into his face...

1233
01:53:11,212 --> 01:53:15,114
broke his nose and jaw and knocked him unconscious on his back.

1234
01:53:16,384 --> 01:53:19,842
By the time somebody come aIong, he'd drowned in his own bIood.

1235
01:53:20,955 --> 01:53:22,946
He was onIy 39 years oId.

1236
01:53:27,562 --> 01:53:29,996
HeIIo? HeIIo?

1237
01:53:31,232 --> 01:53:32,460
HeIIo.

1238
01:53:36,104 --> 01:53:38,095
Was he buried down there?

1239
01:53:38,840 --> 01:53:40,273
We put a stone up.

1240
01:53:40,742 --> 01:53:42,767
He was cremated, like he wanted.

1241
01:53:42,844 --> 01:53:47,110
Half his ashes was interred here, the rest was sent up with his folks.

1242
01:53:48,382 --> 01:53:52,409
He use to say he wanted his ashes scattered on Brokeback Mountain...

1243
01:53:52,487 --> 01:53:54,887
but I wasn't sure where that was.

1244
01:53:55,256 --> 01:53:59,022
I thought Brokeback Mountain might be around where he grew up.

1245
01:53:59,093 --> 01:54:00,390
Knowing Jack...

1246
01:54:00,461 --> 01:54:02,725
it might be some pretend place...

1247
01:54:02,797 --> 01:54:05,994
where bluebirds sing and there's a whiskey spring.

1248
01:54:08,970 --> 01:54:10,403
No, ma'am...

1249
01:54:11,472 --> 01:54:14,600
we was herdin' sheep on Brokeback one summer...

1250
01:54:15,243 --> 01:54:16,642
back in '63.

1251
01:54:26,087 --> 01:54:28,783
Well, he said it was his favorite place.

1252
01:54:30,158 --> 01:54:33,355
l thought he meant to get drunk. He drank a lot.

1253
01:54:36,564 --> 01:54:39,431
ls his folks still up in Lightning Flat?

1254
01:54:40,101 --> 01:54:42,797
They'II be there tiII the day they die.

1255
01:54:47,842 --> 01:54:49,810
Thank you for your time.

1256
01:54:50,678 --> 01:54:52,270
I sure am sorry.

1257
01:54:53,514 --> 01:54:55,277
We was good friends.

1258
01:55:02,456 --> 01:55:04,686
Get in touch with his folks.

1259
01:55:04,759 --> 01:55:08,559
l suppose they'd appreciate it if his wishes was carried out.

1260
01:55:10,398 --> 01:55:12,366
About the ashes, l mean.

1261
01:55:29,183 --> 01:55:30,980
[cows lowing]

1262
01:55:35,189 --> 01:55:36,986
[bird cawing]

1263
01:56:13,160 --> 01:56:16,596
Want a cup of coffee, don't you? Piece of cherry cake?

1264
01:56:16,664 --> 01:56:18,222
Yes, ma'am, l'll have a cup of coffee...

1265
01:56:18,299 --> 01:56:21,462
but l can't eat no cake just now. Thank you.

1266
01:56:30,144 --> 01:56:32,305
l feel awful bad about Jack.

1267
01:56:35,149 --> 01:56:36,480
Thank you.

1268
01:56:38,452 --> 01:56:41,250
l can't begin to tell you how bad l feel.

1269
01:56:44,258 --> 01:56:46,158
(Ennis) l knew him a long time.

1270
01:56:49,063 --> 01:56:51,031
l come by to say that...

1271
01:56:51,699 --> 01:56:55,328
if you want me to take his ashes up there on Brokeback...

1272
01:56:56,070 --> 01:56:58,504
like his wife said he wanted to...

1273
01:56:59,273 --> 01:57:01,070
then l'll be happy to.

1274
01:57:04,178 --> 01:57:05,907
l'll tell you what.

1275
01:57:06,981 --> 01:57:09,381
l know where Brokeback Mountain is.

1276
01:57:10,651 --> 01:57:14,781
Thought he was too goddamn special to be buried in the family plot.

1277
01:57:18,192 --> 01:57:19,921
(John) Jack used to say....

1278
01:57:20,761 --> 01:57:23,423
''Ennis Del Mar,'' he used to say.

1279
01:57:25,099 --> 01:57:28,364
''l'm gonna bring him up here one of these days...

1280
01:57:29,003 --> 01:57:31,938
''and we'll lick this damn ranch into shape.''

1281
01:57:33,374 --> 01:57:35,205
He had some half-baked notion...

1282
01:57:35,276 --> 01:57:37,870
the two of you was gonna move up here...

1283
01:57:38,346 --> 01:57:39,938
build a cabin...

1284
01:57:40,982 --> 01:57:42,711
help run the place.

1285
01:57:46,287 --> 01:57:48,016
Then, this spring...

1286
01:57:49,623 --> 01:57:52,854
he got another fella gonna come up here with him...

1287
01:57:54,528 --> 01:57:57,725
build the place, help run the ranch.

1288
01:57:58,733 --> 01:58:03,170
Some ranch neighbor of his from down in Texas.

1289
01:58:05,239 --> 01:58:08,572
Gonna split up with his wife and come back here...

1290
01:58:09,343 --> 01:58:10,708
so he says.

1291
01:58:12,546 --> 01:58:14,878
But, like most of Jack's ideas...

1292
01:58:16,717 --> 01:58:18,446
never come to pass.

1293
01:58:21,589 --> 01:58:25,457
(mother) l kept his room like it was when he was a boy.

1294
01:58:26,861 --> 01:58:28,988
l think he appreciated that.

1295
01:58:33,534 --> 01:58:36,731
You are welcome to go up to his room, if you want.

1296
01:58:42,410 --> 01:58:44,708
Yeah, l'd like that. Thank you.

1297
01:59:38,132 --> 01:59:39,429
[bird cawing]

1298
02:01:45,893 --> 02:01:47,485
(John) Tell you what.

1299
02:01:49,997 --> 02:01:53,728
We got a family plot. He's goin' in it.

1300
02:01:56,403 --> 02:01:57,665
Yes, sir.

1301
02:02:00,274 --> 02:02:02,572
You come back and see us again.

1302
02:02:16,890 --> 02:02:18,380
Thank you, ma'am.

1303
02:03:13,147 --> 02:03:15,081
@@{radio pIaying]

1304
02:03:16,183 --> 02:03:18,845
(Ennis) Hey there, Junior. Hey, Daddy.

1305
02:03:26,026 --> 02:03:27,425
[car door closing]

1306
02:03:27,695 --> 02:03:28,992
Come here.

1307
02:03:31,799 --> 02:03:33,266
Like the car?

1308
02:03:33,734 --> 02:03:36,532
Yeah. ls it yours? lt's Kurt's.

1309
02:03:37,271 --> 02:03:40,365
l thought you were seein' Troy. Troy?

1310
02:03:40,941 --> 02:03:43,171
Daddy, that was two years ago.

1311
02:03:44,611 --> 02:03:46,909
Troy still playing baseball?

1312
02:03:47,281 --> 02:03:50,478
l don't know what he's doing. l'm seein' Kurt now.

1313
02:03:50,884 --> 02:03:54,047
Well, what does Kurt do? Works out in the oil fields.

1314
02:03:55,823 --> 02:03:59,156
So he's a roughneck, huh? [laughing] Yeah.

1315
02:03:59,993 --> 02:04:03,827
l guess you're 19, you can do whatever you want. lsn't that right?

1316
02:04:03,897 --> 02:04:05,194
Sure.

1317
02:04:10,137 --> 02:04:11,900
[glass tinkling]

1318
02:04:13,807 --> 02:04:16,867
Daddy, you need more furniture. Yeah, well...

1319
02:04:17,511 --> 02:04:20,344
if you got nothin', you don't need nothin'.

1320
02:04:24,618 --> 02:04:26,586
So, what's the occasion?

1321
02:04:31,024 --> 02:04:32,514
Me and Kurt...

1322
02:04:33,827 --> 02:04:35,692
we're getting married.

1323
02:04:38,465 --> 02:04:39,864
Well....

1324
02:04:40,667 --> 02:04:43,192
So how long have you known this guy for?

1325
02:04:43,370 --> 02:04:44,837
About a year.

1326
02:04:46,840 --> 02:04:50,207
Our wedding will be June 5, at the Methodist church.

1327
02:04:50,511 --> 02:04:54,311
Jenny will be singing and Monroe is gonna cater the reception.

1328
02:05:00,788 --> 02:05:02,779
Now this Kurt fella...

1329
02:05:05,125 --> 02:05:06,592
he loves you?

1330
02:05:09,363 --> 02:05:10,955
Yeah, Daddy.

1331
02:05:12,232 --> 02:05:13,631
He loves me.

1332
02:05:21,675 --> 02:05:23,700
Was hopin' you'd be there.

1333
02:05:26,480 --> 02:05:27,606
Yeah.

1334
02:05:30,884 --> 02:05:35,378
l think l'm supposed to be on a roundup down near the Tetons.

1335
02:05:56,310 --> 02:05:57,902
You know what?

1336
02:05:59,246 --> 02:06:02,306
l reckon they can find themselves a new cowboy.

1337
02:06:04,117 --> 02:06:07,644
My little girl, getting married.

1338
02:06:09,223 --> 02:06:10,212
[grunts]

1339
02:06:12,559 --> 02:06:13,821
[bottle thuds]

1340
02:06:21,268 --> 02:06:23,327
To Alma and Kurt.

1341
02:07:43,817 --> 02:07:45,614
Jack, l swear....
